TY  - JOUR
TI  - Stochastic Properties of Fast vs. Slow Growing Economies
AU  - Danthine, Jean-Pierre
AU  - Donaldson, John B.
AB  - [This paper is concerned with characterizing the probability distributions that describe the (stochastic) stationary state of a neoclassical model of optimal growth. In particular, using both theoretical analysis and numerical simulation, we search for systematic relationships between savings (and investment) rates and variability of the economy's aggregates.]
